    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated onion</strong>,<strong> mince</strong>,<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Massage thoroughly, with clean hands, until fully combined, then divide the mixture and roll into 5 meatballs per person</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 8-10 min, turning occasionally, until they are browned (they don't need to be fully cooked through yet!)</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>meatballs</strong> to a plate</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir until a sandy paste forms (if your pan is looking dry add a small knob of butter)</p><p>Whisk the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> into the flour</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until it has thickened slightly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add your <strong>capers</strong> and <strong>clotted cream</strong> to the sauce</p><p>Return the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further until the meatballs are cooked through and the sauce has thickened to a gravy-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>German-style meatballs & creamy caper sauce</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>German-style</strong> <strong>meatballs & creamy caper sauce</strong> from the heat and add a squeeze of<strong> lemon juice</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> roughly, discarding the stems</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper, rip the leaves off, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced spring greens </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, then cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-lean-meatballs-and-creamy-caper-sauce-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spring greens</strong> and<strong> basmati rice</strong> with the <strong>German-style meatballs & creamy caper sauce</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped parsley</strong> and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
